entry.title: TaskAttribution: Move ownership of the tracker to V8PerIsolateData
entry.content:
Continuation preserved embedder data, which is managed by

TaskAttributionTracker, is now tracked per isolate. This CL moves

ownership of TaskAttributionTracker from ThreadScheduler to

V8PerIsolateData, which

- aligns with how CPED is managed

- slightly optimizes getting CPED (avoids TLS access in

ThreadScheduler::Current())

- provides better separation for MBI



This is mostly mechanical:

- ThreadScheduler::Current()->GetTaskAttributionTracker -->

scheduler::TaskAttributionTracker::From(isolate)

- RunningTask(isolate) --> RunningTask()



Main non-mechanical changes:

- Introduce TaskAttributionTracker::From as a helper to get the

tracker from per-isolate data

- Register a TaskAttributionImpl factory method with V8PerIsolateData

in modules_initializer.cc; use that to create the tracker.

Note: this is done to get around layering issues (the tracker is

implemented in modules).



Bug: 1351643

entry.title: [anchor] Use real AnchorEvaluator in UpdateStyleForOutOfFlow
entry.content:
This CL sends the actual AnchorEvaluator(Impl) from OOF layout

into the interleaved style update, which allows anchor()

and anchor-size() queries to compute to their proper values.



In additional to using a real evaluator, we need to integrate with

some of the concepts of our Container Queries implementation:



- Any element with anchor functions are now "interleaving roots"

(ComputedStyle::IsInterleavingRoot), which means "layout upgrades"

automatically do what they need to (e.g. for getComputedStyle and

similar cases).

- The "old style" is stored on PostStyleUpdateScope for every element

with anchor queries, which ensures that we transition from the right

state. See crbug.com/40943044 however, which is not addressed

by this CL.



Also, some of our infamous optimizations are disabled for elements

with anchor queries:



- The matched properties cache can't be used due to implicit anchors.

- The base computed style optimization could probably be used,

but support is deferred to a future CL.



This feature is still behind a separate flag with status:.

Before we can set status:experimental, we need to fix a blocking

crash bug (crbug.com/324930388), and also implement "persistent"

anchor query results, i.e. store the last seen results on Element

and use that for regular style recalcs.

entry.title: Propagate the current transform when creating a side recording
entry.content:
The 2D canvas uses an MemoryManagedPaintRecorder (a child class of

InspectableRecordPaintCanvas) to record draw ops because it needs to

be able to query the current matrix. InspectableRecordPaintCanvas

keeps track of the current matrix by maintaining an SkNoDrawCanvas in

parallel to the recording.



When we open a layer in the 2D canvas, we create a side recording in

which we store the layer content. This is needed so that we could

present the canvas at any time by flushing all paint ops up to the

first beginLayer (opened layers can't be flushed, they'll be presented

later, after they are closed). When creating the side recording

however, the SkNoDrawCanvas of the new recording has to be initialized

with the same matrix as the main recording, or else, the layer's

InspectableRecordPaintCanvas won't hold the correct transform.



The 2D canvas uses a MemoryManagedPaintRecorder, but the

SkNoDrawCanvas lives in the parent class,

InspectableRecordPaintCanvas. MemoryManagedPaintRecorder can't

therefore set the matrix on it's own. The SkNoDrawCanvas is an

implementation detail of InspectableRecordPaintCanvas, it would be

preferable to avoid exposing this via the class API. A better

abstraction is to add CreateChildCanvas constructors, to delegate to

the InspectableRecordPaintCanvas task of creating a canvas with the

same size and matrix.

entry.title: More tests for printing different page sizes to "paper".
entry.content:
When printing to an actual printer (i.e. when not generating a PDF), the

actual paper size needs to be taken into account. If there are @page

rules that request a page size smaller than the actual paper size, the

page should be centered on paper, and margins adjusted (increased)

accordingly. If there are @page rules that request a page size larger

than the actual paper size, the contents should be scaled down

(including margins) to fit on paper, and then centered on paper.

Orientation implied by @page size should also be honored.



We already had some tests, but none of them checked the actual pixel

output. I know this, because I tried to break this functionality on

purpose, and no tests failed. So add some pixel tests, both for @page

sizes smaller and larger than the paper size, and also with flipped

orientation.



(Also, reordering the code in VerifyDefaultPageLayout() to match

parameter order shouldn't upset anyone.)

entry.title: trusted_vault: return the epoch when adding a domain member.
entry.content:
The code currently assumes that, when creating a security domain,

`RegisterDeviceWithoutKeys` is used. The callback to that function

is passed a `TrustedVaultKeyAndVersion` which includes the epoch of the

new security domain (which the server generates).



But, in that context, the key of the `TrustedVaultKeyAndVersion` must be

the all-zeros key, so the only meaningful value _is_ the epoch.



`RegisterAuthenticationFactor` doesn't return the epoch so can only be

used to add a member to an existing security domain where the epoch is

known. But the hw_protected security domain never uses the all-zero key

and thus needs to use `RegisterAuthenticationFactor` to create a

security domain.



Thus the `RegisterAuthenticationFactorCallback` needs an `int` parameter

to communicate the epoch. But then it's essentially the same as the

callback to `RegisterDeviceWithoutKeys`, and so they can be unified.

GetGpuFeatureData() rather than going through IsSkiaGraphiteEnabled().

accurately from the GPU process so remove the base::Feature check

entirely.

entry.title: [Signin][Android] Fix restore metric & use bool for "recorded" status
entry.content:
In https://crrev.com/c/5191994, the magic value of the enum value

RestoreStatus.RESTORE_STATUS_RECORDED has been changed. Since it was

saved to prefs, and used to prevent additional histogram recording.



It has broken the restore metrics Android.RestoreResult, since devices

having old prefs and with the status already recorded consider that

the restore status has not been recorded yet, and records the status

histogram again.



This CL uses a new value for the sign-in timed out metric since the old one is polluted, and introduces a boolean pref used to indicate whether

the restore status has been recorded, to limit similar accident in the future.



Bug: 40075135
